Package: bufferedThresholdPanel
Type: Package
Title: Buffered Panel Threshold Regression with Hysteresis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Messaoud", "Zouikri", email = "mzouikri@parisnanterre.fr",
           role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-6253-9074")),
    person("Faycal", "Hamdi", email = "faycal.hamdi@univ-constantine2.dz",
           role = "aut"),
    person("Said", "Souam", role = "aut"))
Description: Estimates panel data threshold regression models with one or two
    threshold parameters following Hansen (1999) <doi:10.1016/S0304-4076(99)00025-1>
    and Hansen (2000) <doi:10.2307/2669382>. Implements the Buffered Panel
    Threshold Data (BTPD) model of Belarbi et al. (2021)
    <doi:10.1016/j.econmod.2021.02.018>, which extends panel threshold
    regression with a hysteresis (buffer zone) mechanism for smooth transitions
    between regimes. Supports two- and three-regime models, bootstrap inference
    for threshold existence (sequential F1,2 and F2,3 tests), parallel bootstrap
    computation, and publication-ready output tables following the conventions of
    major economics journals. Includes a balanced panel dataset of 92 countries
    (2002-2016) used in Hamdi et al. (2025) <doi:10.1111/twec.70023>.
